TOXIC ALGAE - AUSTRALIA: BLUE-GREEN ALGAE
*****************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Fri 20 Nov 2015
Source The Standard [edited]
http://www.standard.net.au/story/3506977/blue-green-algae-warning/


Water testing has confirmed high concentrations of blue green algae at Camperdown's Lake Bullen Merri. Corangamite Shire is urging the public to avoid all contact with the water, including swimming and fishing.

Sustainable development director Ian Gibb said signs have been installed at the lake to warn people of the high levels of the toxic algae. "Council officers carry out regular inspections and collect samples for lab analysis if there is a visible change in the water," he said.

Corangamite Shire will post regular updates on the status of the lake via its website http://www.corangamite.vic.gov.au.

Mr Gibb said common symptoms of exposure to blue green algae include skin irritation, nausea and vomiting. "Avoid eating any fish caught in the lake, and don't allow pets or livestock to come into contact with the water," he said.

Deep Lake, Lake Tooliorook and Lake Purrumbete are currently considered safe.

